oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Table Rock?
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: unknown
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Snapshots from loose scrapbook pages, dated 1912 and 1914. Includes pictures of Elkmont, Little River, Sunshine Rest Cottage, Table Rock, and swinging bridge. Most of the snapshots had limited or unknown identifications. Five women and one man seated on rock with food. Possibly Table Rock.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Snapshots; Recreation; Great Smoky Mountains; Group portraits; Picnics;
